# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline

## Context

The Transformers.js library already has `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js` (line 8736) with support for 11 model architectures (LLaVa, Florence2, Qwen2-VL, Idefics3/SmolVLM, PaliGemma, Gemma3n, Mistral3, etc.), but there is no corresponding pipeline to expose these models through the `pipeline()` factory function. This means users cannot do `await pipeline('image-text-to-text', modelId)` — the model infrastructure exists but the high-level API is missing.

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `src/pipelines.js` | Add import, JSDoc typedefs, pipeline class, SUPPORTED_TASKS entry, pipeline() JSDoc update |
| `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js` | New test file |

**No changes needed** to `src/models.js` (AutoModelForImageTextToText already exists), `src/transformers.js` (uses `export *` from pipelines.js), or any processor files.

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Add Import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText`

**File:** `src/pipelines.js`, lines 20-45 (import block from `./models.js`)

Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing import. Insert after `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction` (line 43):

```javascript
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,     // ← ADD
    PreTrainedModel,
```

### Step 2: Add JSDoc Typedefs and Pipeline Class

**File:** `src/pipelines.js`  
**Location:** Insert after `ImageToTextPipeline` (after line 2005), before `ImageClassificationSingle` typedef (line 2007)

#### JSDoc Typedefs:
```javascript
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Generate text given image(s) and a text prompt.
 * @param {ImagePipelineInputs} images The image(s) to use as context.
 * @param {string} [text] The text prompt to use.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput|ImageTextToTextOutput[]>} An object (or array of objects) containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */
```

#### Pipeline Class:
```javascript
/**
 * Image-Text-to-Text pipeline using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline generates
 * text from image(s) and an optional text prompt, supporting vision-language models.
 *
 * **Example:** Generate a description w/ `Xenova/llava-1.5-7b-hf`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'Xenova/llava-1.5-7b-hf');
 * const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const output = await pipe(url, 'Describe this image in detail.');
 * // [{ generated_text: '...' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(images, text = null, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(images);

        const processor_outputs = await this.processor(preparedImages, text);

        const output = await this.model.generate({
            ...processor_outputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        });

        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));

        return decoded;
    }
}
```

